    "goal_orientation": "0.0",
    "role": "",
    "instruction": "Step 1 — Ingest: Accept credit agreement document (PDF/DOCX/TXT). Classify document type (original agreement, amendment letter, rate notice). Parse document structure including recitals, definitions, article-level provisions, and schedules. Extract mandatory fields per the loan reference data schema: facility type, currency, maturity date, SOFR spread, compounding convention, fallback language, margin grid, covenant definitions, and agent bank identifiers. Assign a confidence score to each extracted field and record the source citation (page number and clause reference).\n\nStep 2 — Validate: Query the Loan Administration System (Loan IQ / WSO) for the existing loan record using the deal identifier. Perform a field-by-field comparison between extracted values and system-of-record values. Apply business rules including: SOFR spread reasonableness checks, maturity date consistency, floating rate type-to-benchmark mapping validation, and compounding convention alignment with ARRC guidelines. Score each discrepancy by severity: Critical, Warning, or Informational.\n\nStep 3 — Reconcile: Auto-populate high-confidence, non-conflicting fields to the loan data staging layer for downstream system update. Route low-confidence or conflicting fields to the operations exception queue with full supporting evidence including extracted value, system value, confidence score, and source citation. Do not overwrite existing system-of-record values without operator confirmation for Critical-severity discrepancies.\n\nStep 4 — Report and Log: Emit a structured reconciliation report summarising extraction throughput, fields auto-populated, exceptions raised by severity, and STP rate. Write all events — document receipt, extraction output, validation decisions, exception routing, and operator overrides — to the immutable audit ledger with timestamps. Escalate critical exceptions that remain unresolved after 24 hours. Return structured JSON output to the calling system.",
